# Descrition

Since the X-Frame-Options are set with "SAMEORIGIN" value, still possible framing hiself, this is helpful to get values of another page, so i use it to get some values of `/widgets/twitter_registrations/edit`. in edit page we have a hidden input with name `authenticity_token` that is a CSRF token, so i need this token to perform a CSRF to change personal data.

using the following script in any other page in www.twitterflightschool.com, we can get the `authenticity_token` from edit page:
```
document.body.innerHTML="<iframe id=ifr src=/widgets/twitter_registrations/edit></iframe>";
setTimeout(function(){
 alert(ifr.contentDocument.getElementsByName("authenticity_token")[0].value);
},1337);
```

ok, now that we have the CSRF token it is easier to assemble the rest of the PoC, which is basically used the previous PoC template. We just need to recreate a fetch request with two new data values, authenticity_token and user[custom_a], user [custom_a] is where the recovery email is sent and thats it!

